              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "VDG"
                ],
                "institute": "4UKRUFT"
              },
              "free_text": [
                "Electrostatic accelerator with maximum",
                "energy 4 MeV and energy dispersion of beam 400 eV.",
                "A beam current  was 10-15 microA."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The isotopic target of 40Ar is produced by hammering",
                "of 40Ar+ ions in tantalum backing directly in",
                "electromagnetic separator. The target thickness was",
                "about 4 keV at proton energy at Ep=2.0 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A germanium- lithium detector is  used with an",
                "active volume of  63 cm**3 and a resolution of 3.0 keV",
                "at Eg=1.33 MeV. The detector was calibrated with",
                "standard sources and using gamma-rays  from reaction",
                "27Al(p,gamma)28Si at Ep=991.86 keV. For reduction of",
                "the background from low energy gamma-rays the detector",
                "was shielded with Pb and Cu. The gamma-rays were",
                "detected  at angles of 0, 30, 45, 60, 90 degrees",
                "concerning proton beam direction."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "NAICR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "  NaI(Tl) detector was used for  excitation",
                "function measurements  and  as monitor of gamma",
                "radiation. The dimensions of the crystal  was",
                "diameter 15 x 10 cm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "In REACTIONs FCT=1/(2Jp+1)(2Jt+1),",
                "where is Jp = spin of incident projectile and",
                "Jt = spin of target nucleus.",
                "In the formula of resonance strength:",
                "          g*Gamma(i)Gamma(j)/Gamma(tot)",
                "instead of usual statistical weight:",
                "  g=(2J+1)/(2Jp+1)(2Jt+1), the authors used g=(2J+1)"
              ]
            }
          ],
